<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/80601AKMRNLTTLLDPKKJNNMTCGCVKGPLC> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Alex MacKenzie's Hungry for Laughs";
  schema:description """
	Canada’s Funniest Comedy Tour is back and it’s definitely a night worth leaving the house for! The Hungry for Laughs Comedy Tour is rolling into town with an all-star lineup of comedians who have been featured on Amazon Prime, Netflix, Just for Laughs, Canada’s Got Talent, CBC’s The Debaters, and more.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Founded by Alex Mackenzie and produced by ECL Productions, this isn’t your typical comedy show it’s an experience built around laughter, connection, and giving back.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>To date, the tour has raised over $65,000 for local charities across Canada, and every ticket purchased continues that impact. When you come to the show, you’re not just having an incredible night out you’re supporting your community.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Expect a high energy, feel good night filled with big laughs, crowd interaction, and unforgettable moments. With hundreds of hours poured into every show, the goal is simple: you won’t just remember the jokes but you’ll remember how the show made you feel.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If you love stand-up comedy, want a night out that actually leaves you feeling better, and believe in supporting something bigger than yourself this show was made for you.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Come laugh out loud, give back, and leave feeling Never Been Better. Stand up to hunger. It’s no laughing matter.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Comedians:<span><br/></span>Alex Mackenzie - Amazon Prime, Melbourne Comedy Festival<span><br/></span>Ola Dada - Just for Laughs, Canada's Got Talent, Sirius XM Top Comic <span><br/></span>Brittany Lyseng - CBC Debaters, Just for Laughs, Roast Battle Canada<span><br/></span>Efthimios Nasiopoulous - Just for Laughs, Sirius XM, CBC Comedy<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-21T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
