<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/77401ATDSDLQCDJCLVLHGVLTPSDBJPPBK> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "COFFEE CONCERT: Sarah Hagen";
  schema:description """
	Morning Concert with Coffee & Treats – Classical Music<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://porttheatre.com/events/series/coffee-concerts\">Enjoy all six shows</a> throughout the season with the <span class=\"BoldText\">Coffee Concerts 6-Pack</span>: $225 ($45 Savings). <span class=\"ItalicText\">Limited availability. These tickets sell fast!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A classical pianist with a wry wit, <span class=\"BoldText\">Sarah Hagen</span> enjoys a rich and diverse concertizing life across Canada and internationally, including twice to New York City’s Carnegie Hall. Highlights of recent seasons include solo sets at Expo in Osaka, Tønder Festival in Denmark, Cambridge Folk Festival, and Mariposa Folk Festival and tours throughout Sweden, the UK, and the USA. Her interpretations have been described as \"<span class=\"ItalicText\">outstandingly inventive,</span>” “<span class=\"ItalicText\">played flawlessly,</span>” and “<span class=\"ItalicText\">with great sensitivity and heart.</span>” <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Sarah has released four albums. Her most recent recording of Bach’s Goldberg Variations was described by Whole Note magazine as “something to absolutely die for” and was the recipient of two Music PEI awards and two ECMA nominations. She is the recipient of Music PEI’s 2025 Award for Achievement in Classical Music. Awarded as Artist of the Year by Ontario Contact and the BC Touring Council, Sarah brings to the stage her unique combination of piano and humour.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“<span class=\"ItalicText\">…the level of passion that Hagen possesses — when it comes to experiencing, interpreting and expressing art — is something quite extraordinary.</span>” - <span class=\"BoldText\">The Guardian</span> (Charlottetown)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“<span class=\"ItalicText\">We listened in raptures. Sarah Hagen, from Canada, plays exquisitely.</span>” - <span class=\"BoldText\">Cambs News, UK</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-24T10:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
