<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/73001AVCMHLKGJVPNKDTRBKJNMCBVTBRQ> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Crash Test Dummies - JINGLE ALL THE WAY";
  schema:description """
	With one of the most memorable voices in Canadian Music history, alternative folk rock band, the Crash Test Dummies are coming to the Island in November.   <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The Crash Test Dummies are a three time Grammy nominated and Juno award winning group who soared to the top of the worldwide charts in the early 1990's with a multitude of unforgettable songs. Songs like “The Ballad of Peter Pumpkin Head” , “Hmmm Hmmm”, “Superman's Song”, “Androgynous” and many more. All of these releases keep the same folk based alternative spirit of their early sound centering around the distinct baritone of front man Brad Roberts and Ellen Reid's folk-rock infusion.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>At their appearance in November, being so close to the holiday season, the tour is called Crash Test Dummies – Jingle All the Way and features all of their biggest hits interspersed with seasonal favorites done in the famous CTD style. The show promises to be the fun Christmas show of the Year.<span><br/></span>   <span><br/></span>Special guest opening for this show will be Logan Richard.<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-17T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
