<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/85601ATTRSQHQPBGNRTKLKJJMRLPJKPBR> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Love Can Build a Bridge";
  schema:description """
	Celebrate the music, legacy, and enduring bond of one of country music's most beloved families with <span class=\"BoldText\">Love Can Build a Bridge – The Judds & Wynonna Experience</span>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Featuring timeless classics including <span class=\"BoldText\">\"Mama He's Crazy,\" \"Why Not Me,\" \"Grandpa (Tell Me 'Bout the Good Old Days),\"</span> and <span class=\"BoldText\">\"Love Can Build a Bridge,\"</span> along with Wynonna's chart-topping solo hits <span class=\"BoldText\">\"No One Else on Earth,\" \"Tell Me Why,\"</span> and <span class=\"BoldText\">\"Rock Bottom,\"</span> this live theatre concert captures the unmistakable harmonies, heartfelt storytelling, and powerful performances that made The Judds one of country music's most iconic acts.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Starring<span><br/></span>Jóna Kristinsson</span> as <span class=\"BoldText\">Wynonna Judd</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Allison Barlow</span> as <span class=\"BoldText\">Naomi Judd</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Featuring Some of Vancouver Island's Finest Musicians<span><br/></span>Al Medcalf</span> – Guitar<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Stewart McLellan</span> – Guitar, Pedal Steel & Vocals<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Howard Anderson</span> – Keyboards, Saxophone & Vocals<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">James Van Veerden</span> – Bass<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Trevor Manuel</span> – Drums<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Sylvia Humble</span> – Backing Vocals<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Together, this exceptional cast of performers and musicians brings the unmistakable sound of The Judds and Wynonna to life with authenticity, passion, and extraordinary musicianship. From soaring harmonies and heartfelt ballads to high-energy country anthems, audiences will experience a live theatrical concert that celebrates one of country music's most beloved legacies.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">More Than a Tribute... It's a Celebration.</span><span><br/></span>More than a tribute, Love Can Build a Bridge – The Judds & Wynonna Experience is a celebration of family, resilience, and the timeless music that has touched generations. Featuring exceptional live musicianship, heartfelt storytelling, and unforgettable performances, this theatrical concert experience honours the legacy of Naomi and Wynonna Judd while celebrating the songs that continue to bring audiences together.<span><br/></span>Join us for an unforgettable evening of world-class live music, cherished memories, and the enduring spirit of <span class=\"BoldText\">The Judds and Wynonna.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xft4YqffQ8M\"> Love Can Build A Bridge</a>
""";
