<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/74001ADSVJLCKPMSPGQBKPTQSCGRSRDKK> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "MOONDANCE: The Van Morrison Songbook";
  schema:description """
	at St. Andrew's United Church<span><br/></span>315 Fitzwilliam Street, Nanaimo<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Mystic Celtic Soul singer and songwriter Van Morrison has placed his indelible stamp upon Western Music culture with a career spanning over half a century!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>As the voice of “Van the Man” <span class=\"BoldText\">Bruce Coughlan</span> (ISSA International Singer Songwriter Award Top Male Vocalist 2024) brings one of his major influences to life with an uncanny ability to make you shut your eyes and think the great Van is in the room.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The band with Bruce includes some of the top musicians on Canada’s West Coast including Tiller’s Folly bandmate <span class=\"BoldText\">Laurence Knight</span> (Bass and Vocals), <span class=\"BoldText\">Greg Stuart</span> (Drums and Vocals), <span class=\"BoldText\">Lee Worden</span> (Keys, Guitar, Vocals), <span class=\"BoldText\">Karen Graves</span> (Saxes, flute and vocals), and <span class=\"BoldText\">Geeta Das</span> (Trumpet).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>These musicians have performed with Michael Buble, Colin James, Adele, Ian Tyson, Long John Baldry, Shari Ulrich, Jim Byrnes, Mike Reno, Taj Mahal, Roy Forbes, Corb Lund and more!
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-09-26T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/files/e039df0e-de1e-4b8f-82ec-7529ba521f58.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/theporttheatre/location/412AHMGMKLQDMMDQBVNMGMNLDCBBPTLQP>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/theporttheatre/organization/got-pop?-concerts>;
  schema:offers _:57e8ee661ad740a08e5ad0ea20bc4b345004;
  schema:keywords "Offsite Events";
