<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/84601APCQHMGHKKSGKBJLBVSJRRCQDJTV> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "She Composed, Herself";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"ItalicText\">“The piano in her mother’s salon was never meant to be a musical instrument. It is meant to be dusted, and polished, and admired. Like the girl herself, it is meant to be seen, not heard…”</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">She Composed, Herself</span> celebrates the life and music of the late-19th-century female French composer, Mel (Mélanie) Bonis. Spoken-word intersects with soaring cello and tumultuous piano as the extraordinary story of this remarkable woman unfolds — a story of high drama and intrigue of Bridgertonian proportions… arranged marriages, passionate affairs, a secret daughter… and more. She Composed, Herself shines the spotlight on one of history’s hidden female influencers.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Brought to life by the Quill & Scroll Ensemble:<span><br/></span>Alexandra Lee - Cellist and Artistic Director<span><br/></span>Rachel Dunstan Muller - Writer and Storyteller <span><br/></span>Frances Armstrong - Pianist and Collaborator<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Original script by Rachel Dunstan Muller <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Musical excerpts arranged by Alexandra Lee:<span><br/></span>Sonata in F, Op. 67, for cello & piano, by Mel Bonis<span><br/></span>Méditation, Op. 33, by Mel Bonis Les Gitanos, by Mel Bonis<span><br/></span>Noël pastoral, by Mel Bonis Berceuse, by Mel Bonis<span><br/></span>La Cathédrale blessée, by Mel Bonis Clair de Lune, by Claude Debussy<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://alexandralee.ca/she\\-composed-herself\"> www.alexandralee.ca/she-composed-herself</a><span><br/></span>Instagram: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/shecomposedherself\"> shecomposedherself</a> <span><br/></span>Facebook: <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61584837413211\"> She Composed, Herself</a> 
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-10-10T14:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/files/2d4d4748-b5a0-4c1e-8f71-b303a5611d84.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/theporttheatre/location/407AGBMNMGJMSNPVKJMSNVLRPHJBTDPHT>;
