<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/91201ALKRLHGDGHKMCRKDBJKSBNPKJQGR> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Shelter - A Play Reading";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"ItalicText\">Shelter</span>, written by local playwright and award-winning actor, <span class=\"BoldText\">Jim Maher</span>, is a new play in development being presented by <span class=\"BoldText\">Western Edge Theatre</span> as a staged reading in the Port Theatre lobby. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The story follows a mother and son locked in an underground bunker who are taking shelter from a worldwide nuclear fallout. Unfortunately, the father of the family did not make it into the shelter having passed away after loading the bunker with supplies for three. Fortunately, that means that mother and son should have more food with only two and if they ration, they can survive for quite some time down there… Unfortunately, they quickly discover someone has been eating their food. In an incredible twist of fate, the man eating their food is none other than President Alexander Vane, the man responsible for setting the world on fire. After tying him up and resizing their portions to last long enough, (after the President had greedily ate more than a fair share), can the two navigate their emotions and morality and keep a monster alive in their shelter? What would you do if you were in their shelter? Are you worth saving? <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Join this witty, dark-comedy/drama at Western Edge’s staged reading. Enjoy the negotiations of values and ethics in this thought-provoking new original work. The readers of the play include an array of all local award winning actors - Sophie Maher, Jake Rysz, and Dean Chadwick.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-07-25T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/files/96774b4d-c33b-485b-8d66-da62042f9724.jpg>;
