    schema:Event;
  schema:name "SIZZLE: Calls of the Wild";
  schema:description """
	Join the VIS horn section - Horns of Plenty - as they perform a variety of fun and eclectic music, ranging from fanfares and operas to hunting calls and movie scores. They will explore the history of the horn, demonstrating with different instruments: natural horns, post horns, modern horns and an Alphorn!  Come be transported from the hunt to the hall and enjoy this horn quartet journey.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>MUSICIANS<span><br/></span>Horns: Andrew Clark, Heather Walker, Karen Hough, Joanna Schulz<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>PROGRAMME*<span><br/></span>HAYDEN: Symphony 31, Horn Signal Fanfare<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Four Hunting Calls from an English Collection c.1758<span><br/></span>The Call in the Morning<span><br/></span>The View <span><br/></span>The Soil<span><br/></span>The Death<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The Alphorn<span><br/></span>J. M. MOLTER: Symphony in C Major <span><br/></span>E. HUMPERDINK: Hansel and Gretel Overture                     <span><br/></span>C.M VON WEBER: Der Freischütz, Hunting Chorus<span><br/></span>TCHAIKOVSKY: Waltz of the Flowers<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Friedrich HOMILIUS (1813-1902): Quartet Op.38<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>John Williams Movie Medley<span><br/></span>Londonderry Air<span><br/></span>Rainbow Connection<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>*programming subject to change<span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-07-22T19:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
