<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/74801ATMBGSKMPNBVPKBRVQTPBHBSVTTR> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "SPOTLIGHT: Sophie's Surprise 29th";
  schema:description """
	UK CIRCUS & PARTY MAYHEM (Age 16+)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>It’s Sophie’s 29th birthday party, and you’re invited… but don’t tell Sophie!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>It’s circus. It’s comedy. It’s chaos. <span class=\"ItalicText\">Sophie’s Surprise 29th</span> features world-leading performers from Cirque du Soleil, La Clique, The 7 Fingers and more. This talented cast will make you believe you’re one of the guests for a superb ninety minutes of cheeky fun. Six world-leading entertainers perform death-defying circus mixed with a 90s house party, set to a pumping soundtrack of old faves. This style of cabaret entertainment is the perfect night out, and when Sophie shows up, even she’s amazed at what’s going on.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>As an audience member, prepare to be part of this wild birthday bash! If you’ve ever been to a surprise party, you know the anticipation of waiting for the guest of honour to arrive. In <span class=\"ItalicText\">Sophie’s Surprise 29th</span>, the cast does an excellent job of getting the fun started. Party hits are playing, and they’re passing out party hats, spraying glitter, and Lynx Body Spray around, and a shady character is dealing what appear to be Jammie Dodgers. It’s clear from the outset that this is going to be an epic party.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“<span class=\"ItalicText\">Young company, Three Legged Race Productions, has created a show that stands out by being so joyfully crass that you can’t help but love it. The concept is simple: we’re at a party, possibly in the late 90’s/early 2000’s, with a selection of misfits and weirdos. There’s a chav, a goth, a party girl, the “ugly” girl, the cool chick, and the drug dealer. Each character is clearly defined from the outset, and all play their roles to perfection. But there’s a circus alongside the comedy, and each performer does an excellent job of showing off their skills.</span>” — Frodo Allan, <span class=\"BoldText\">Broadway Baby</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“<span class=\"ItalicText\">Thrilling…There are shocks aplenty as daredevils perform death-defying acts</span>”<span><br/></span>—Brian Logan, <span class=\"BoldText\">The Guardian</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-10-28T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/files/3a0cfaeb-28ee-4e32-9e3a-d9da511d1f00.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/theporttheatre/location/407AGBMNMGJMSNPVKJMSNVLRPHJBTDPHT>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/theporttheatre/organization/the-port-theatre-society>;
  schema:offers _:57e8ee661ad740a08e5ad0ea20bc4b345094;
  schema:keywords "Circus";
  schema:duration "PT90M";
  schema:endDate "2026-10-28T21:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

